The Congressional Medal of Honor Society is so named because that is the name it was given in an act of Congress signed into law by President Eisenhower on August 5, 1958 as Title 36, Chapter 33 of the U.S. Code. (See .) The law authorizing the society has since been transferred to Title 36, Chapter 405 of the U.S. Code.↩
