It is considered proper to render a salute to a Medal of Honor recipient when otherwise inappropriate, e.g. officer saluting enlisted and enlisted saluting enlisted, although it is not universally prescribed. For example, neither Army Regulation 600-25 or Navy Regulations Chapter 12 mention this exception. When rendering a salute in this circumstance, the superior often renders the salute to be simultaneous with the junior, as the salute is being rendered to the Medal itself, and not the recipient's rank.↩
